\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. P. tricuspidata} (Siebold & Zucc.) Planchon in A. & C. DC.,{\i  Monogr. Phan.}{\b  5}: 452 (1887). Stems up to 20 m, climbing. Leaves on old plants mostly suborbicular-deltate in outline, with 3 acuminate lobes, but on young shoots some 3-foliolate and some simple, unlobed leaves may occur. Tendrils short, much-branched, clinging by preformed adhesive discs. Inflorescences as in {\b 1}, but mostly on short shoots. Fruit with 1-2 seeds. {\i Widely cultivated for ornament on walls; naturalized in Jugoslavia and perhaps elsewhere}. [Ju.] ({\i China and Japan}.)
