\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves simple, alternate; stipules usually caducous. Flowers hermaphrodite, actinomorphic, 5-merous. Sepals and petals free. Stamens numerous, sometimes united at the base into fascicles. Ovary superior, of 5 carpels; fruit a capsule or nut.
