\pard\f0\fs28  {\b  Corchorus olitorius}  L.,{\i  Sp. Pl. }529 (1753), extensively cultivated in warmer countries for its fibres and as a vegetable, is occasionally cultivated in the Aegean region and has been reported as locally naturalized or casual. It is an erect, glabrous annual with ovate, serrate leaves, small, yellow, leaf-opposed flowers and a narrow, many-seeded capsule.
